Among us, I think there would be no lack of conversation prompts. I have 
a few topics:

1. Would it be desirable to create an English Academy, modeled on the 
Academie Française? Would it even be possible?

2. If the Read Alphabet were widely adopted, might we no longer see the 
value of standardization, in favor of spelling how you speak? Is this a 
bad thing or a good thing?

3. One way to standardize phonetic spelling to standardize a proper 
manner of speaking. (I think this refers back to question 1). Should one 
accent be considered &quot;standard&quot;?And which one? And why?


